<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Biographical Information
</head>
<p>An act was passed by the General Assembly on 18 February 1817 entitled an act arranging the counties into districts for the election of senators and for equalizing the land tax. A similar act was passed on 24 March 1838 providing for the reassessment of lands in the Commonwealth. These acts established a board of principal assessors of four members for the newly created four districts. These acts also called for the appointment of assistant assessors in every county appointed by the Executive and recommended by the county court.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>The Records of the Principal &amp; Assistant Assessors are arranged into two series. Series have been designated for Principal &amp; Assistant Assessors. These records document the recommendation, application, and sometimes commission of the principal &amp; assistant assessors of the land tax in 1817 and 1838.
</p>
</scopecontent>
